==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palmistry
<hw>Pal`mis*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Palmister</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art or practice of
divining or telling fortunes, or of judging of character, by the lines
and marks in the palm of the hand; chiromancy.</def>
<rj><au>Ascham.</au> <au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dexterous use or trick of the hand.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palmitate</ent>⟦br⟧
